A memory leak happens when a program allocates memory but never releases it, even though itâ€™s no longer needed.
	â€¢ This causes memory usage to grow over time â†’ system slows down or crashes.
	â€¢ Common in long-running apps like web servers, desktop apps, or services.
	â€¢ Example in C#:
		â—‹ Subscribing to an event but never unsubscribing.
		â—‹ Holding references in a static collection.
ğŸ‘‰ In simple terms: Memory leak is like borrowing books from the library and never returning themâ€”the library eventually runs out of space.

